cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with the evaluation and comparison of routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks. It may also belong to "cs.IT" (Information Theory) as it involves the analysis of communication systems. Additionally, it could be categorized under "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with distributed routing protocols. "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible sub-category as mobile ad hoc networks involve social interactions between nodes. Finally, "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) is a potential sub-category as security is an important aspect of routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks.
